 <!-- How to calculate -->
 <section style="padding:3rem 1.5rem;background:var(--color-card-bg);border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);">
 <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
 <h2 class="section-h2">
 How to find your life path number
 </h2>
 <p class="text-muted-text leading-relaxed mb-6">
 To find your life path number, reduce your full birth date to a single digit - or a master number. Write out your date of birth as three parts: month, day, and year. Reduce each to a single digit, add them together, and reduce again.
 </p>
 <div class="card-light p-6 mb-6">
 <div class="font-bold text-body-text mb-4 font-[family-name:var(--font-family-heading)]">
 Example: July 26, 1964
 </div>
 <div class="space-y-2 text-sm font-mono">
 <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
 <span class="text-violet font-bold w-16 shrink-0">Month:</span>
 <span class="text-muted-text">7 (July = 7)</span>
 </div>
 <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
 <span class="text-violet font-bold w-16 shrink-0">Day:</span>
 <span class="text-muted-text">2 + 6 = 8</span>
 </div>
 <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
 <span class="text-violet font-bold w-16 shrink-0">Year:</span>
 <span class="text-muted-text">1 + 9 + 6 + 4 = 20 → 2 + 0 = 2</span>
 </div>
 <div class="border-t border-border/40 pt-2 mt-2 flex items-center gap-2">
 <span class="text-gold font-bold w-16 shrink-0">Total:</span>
 <span class="text-body-text font-bold">7 + 8 + 2 = 17 → 1 + 7 = <span class="text-violet">8</span></span>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>
 <p class="text-muted-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
 One rule to remember: if your reduction gives you 11, 22, or 33 at any stage, stop. These are master numbers and aren't reduced further.
 </p>
 <p class="text-muted-text leading-relaxed">
 Want step-by-step examples for every possible scenario?
 <a href="/learn/how-to-calculate-life-path-number/" class="text-violet hover:underline font-medium">Read the full calculation guide →</a>
 </p>
 </div>
